This paper is about learning activation functions in neural networks, which is a topic closely related to neural network architectures and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes a new method for learning activation functions, which involves adding local subnetworks to the neural network. This approach is related to the design of neural network architectures, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on various tasks, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a method for optimizing neural networks, which is related to the field of control systems, suggesting that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category.
